Program: Outlook
Title: 19/10/2010
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00b9f95
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 20 Oct 2010
MISSING CHINESE CHILDREN In China up to 70,000 youngsters are reported missing each year. Jo Fidgen hears the remarkable story of one boy, Christian, who was adopted by an American woman and moved to the US but who was reunited with his birth parents eleven years later. BELL-RINGING BROTHERS Outlook reporter Dany Mitzman visits the small Northern Italian town of Chiari to meet the brothers who are bringing the ancient art of bell-ringing into the 21st Century. SARFRAZ MANZOOR The British Pakistani journalist talks about his family's reaction when he chose to marry a non-Muslim. Show less